Key Match Events: Glasgow scored a penalty for Guyana in the 43rd minute.
van der Kust scored for Suriname in the 18th minute.
Montnor scored for Suriname in the 66th minute.
Misidjan scored for Suriname in the 83rd minute.
Montnor received yellow cards in the 79th and 81st minutes.
Pre-Game Insights: Guyana is making their first appearance in the top tier of the CONCACAF Nations League.
Guyana was promoted from League B by finishing three points above Puerto Rico.
Suriname avoided relegation from League A by claiming five points in their four group fixtures.
Guyana is currently ranked 154th by FIFA.
Guyana needs a top-two finish to advance into the knockout phase and a top-four place to avoid relegation.
Guyana won all five of their League B fixtures last year under the guidance of Jamal Shabazz.
Suriname has not lost in three matches played across all competitions since the appointment of Stanley Menzo in March.
Suriname has only suffered one defeat in their previous seven matches played across all competitions.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at the Synthetic Track and Field Facility in Leonora.
Guyana came from behind to win three of their 2023 matches when conceding the opener.
Suriname has not won an away match against Guyana since June 2008.
